Actually an even simpler solution would be to create a ZipArchiveStreamFactory which extends ArchiveStreamFactory and simply overwrite the createArchiveInputStream function. That would make it so there wouldn't need to be any change to PackageParser at all - just a new class created in commons-compress

All the client would have to do is create that ZipArchiveStreamFactory, set the allowStoredEntriesWithDataDescriptor to true, and set that in the ParseContext and it should then use that to create the data descriptor enabled ZipArchiveInputStream.

What you think about that @tballison @PeterAlfredLee ?

